  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (a44159a 2023-01-03T00:04:41.810446Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge fmt\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nSetting `fmt.variable_override_spacing` to `false` does nothing. Just try to use it on the following code:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\npragma solidity >=0.6.0 <0.9.0;\r\n\r\ncontract Base1 {\r\n    function foo() public virtual { }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Base2 {\r\n    function foo() public virtual { }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Inherited is Base1, Base2 {\r\n    // Derives from multiple bases defining foo(), so we must explicitly override it\r\n    function foo() public override (Base1, Base2) { }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt will keep the spacing between `override` and `(Base1`, and it will re-add it if you delete it yourself.",
